java:
    *it is a object oriented programing  language
    *its also know as write once read anywhare
        use of Jvm java can read any os that contiains jvm mechine 
    *platform independent;
    
    .java----->.class----->machinecode
compiler:

    it convert .java to .class(byte code)
 jvm:
 
    JAVA VITUAL MACHINE;
    it convert byte code to machine code;
    
    
 JRE:
    JAVA RUNTIME  ENVIRONMENT   
    it contains jvm and java libraries;
 
 JDK:
    JAVA DEVELOPEMENT KIT
    It contains jre and mechine tools and compiler;
    
 DATA TYPES:
     PREMITIVE-byte ,short,int,long,double,float,char,boolean;
     WRAPPER-byte==>Byte;short-->Short;int-->Integer;long-->Long;double-->Double;float-->Float;char-->character;boolean-->Boolean;
    
 VARIABLES:
      variables are containers that store data in memory;    
     
     int age = 25;                  // Integer variable  

String name = "Java";          // String variable  

double salary = 50000.50;      // Double variable  
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
     
        